  <page id="2329">
    <name>Everyone Uses Math </name>
    <intro></intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{81454e21-9569-4b9d-9ba7-bb4e569b83d7}{88}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Math.png?time=1672695918350" alt="" width="300" height="486" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_right"&gt;Everyone uses math.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;For example, when driving, we “figure out” how&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;many more miles to the next turn. When cooking, we may need to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;double or halve a recipe. When working out,&amp;nbsp;we figure out how many&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;more repetitions to do before we finish. We often figure out how much&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;time&amp;nbsp;it will&amp;nbsp;take to reach a destination, or how much time is left in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;class.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{81454e21-9569-4b9d-9ba7-bb4e569b83d7}{91}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Although they use math regularly, many adult learners have a negative&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;mindset about their academic abilities in general and&amp;nbsp;math, in particular.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Think of how often you hear learners in your class say, “I am&amp;nbsp;not good at&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;math” or “I&amp;nbsp;don't&amp;nbsp;do any math because there is no use for it in what I do.”&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{81454e21-9569-4b9d-9ba7-bb4e569b83d7}{94}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:902,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;a data-sessionid="9d1d596d-a4ef-429a-824c-5a719ee6c97d" data-shapeids="7" data-slide=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Additional%20Resources%20%281%29.png" alt="" width="68" height="66" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_middle"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Resource&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.luminafoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/stem.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;STEM Center on Education and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Workforce&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;, learn about workplace demands for science,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;technology, and math&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{81454e21-9569-4b9d-9ba7-bb4e569b83d7}{94}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:902,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:6,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider%20wave.png" alt="Divider Wave" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
